00:19:46.389 --> 00:19:52.852
Question number 10: The
American educational system

00:19:52.852 --> 00:19:55.586
is broken in many ways,
but we also have a problem

00:19:55.586 --> 00:19:57.654
of misallocation of
resources in that highly

00:19:57.654 --> 00:19:59.929
educated minds gravitate
towards hedge funds,

00:19:59.929 --> 00:20:01.814
investment banks and other
lucrative professions

00:20:01.814 --> 00:20:03.788
and away from teaching
and other professions

00:20:03.788 --> 00:20:05.736
that are more productive
for society as a whole.

00:20:05.736 --> 00:20:08.388
Given your highly relevant
personal career shift,

00:20:08.388 --> 00:20:09.502
do you have any ideas

00:20:09.502 --> 00:20:12.229
about how to change that misallocation?

00:20:12.229 --> 00:20:17.503
I think people go into a
career for multiple reasons.

00:20:17.503 --> 00:20:21.000
I think one is intellectual stimulation.

00:20:21.000 --> 00:20:24.205
Teaching is as, or more,
intellectually stimulating

00:20:24.205 --> 00:20:26.416
than many of those other
higher paid careers.

00:20:26.416 --> 00:20:28.535
They go into something for compensation,

00:20:28.535 --> 00:20:30.076
and that's something where,

00:20:30.076 --> 00:20:32.003
at least definitely at
the K through 12 level,

00:20:32.003 --> 00:20:34.668
there isn't that compensation.

00:20:34.668 --> 00:20:37.203
They also go into it for respect.

00:20:37.203 --> 00:20:39.935
The one example I give here is professors.

00:20:39.935 --> 00:20:43.337
There isn't any crisis about great minds

00:20:43.337 --> 00:20:46.666
going into academia, even though academia

00:20:46.666 --> 00:20:50.465
really has, the compensation academia

00:20:50.465 --> 00:20:52.534
even though it's just
as competitive to become

00:20:52.534 --> 00:20:53.989
a tenured professor at a great university,

00:20:53.989 --> 00:20:55.357
or actually more competitive to become

00:20:55.357 --> 00:20:56.589
a tenured professor at a university

00:20:56.589 --> 00:20:58.810
than make partner at a prestigious bank

00:20:58.810 --> 00:21:00.201
or hedge fund or private equity firm,

00:21:00.201 --> 00:21:02.667
you still have a lot of
people going into academia

00:21:02.667 --> 00:21:04.873
despite the lack of compensation.

00:21:04.873 --> 00:21:06.334
They make more than K through 12 teachers,

00:21:06.334 --> 00:21:09.670
but nowhere near what those
same people would make

00:21:09.670 --> 00:21:11.071
if they went into industry.

00:21:11.071 --> 00:21:13.338
I think the reason why
really, really, really

00:21:13.338 --> 00:21:14.906
smart people, and not
say that really, really

00:21:14.906 --> 00:21:16.405
smart people aren't going to K through 12,

00:21:16.405 --> 00:21:18.471
but it's just their threshold of passion

00:21:18.471 --> 00:21:20.568
has to be so high that it
overcomes these other things;

00:21:20.568 --> 00:21:23.733
but the reason why you
have less of a problem

00:21:23.733 --> 00:21:26.655
in the higher education
is I think you have

00:21:26.655 --> 00:21:29.783
a high degree of respect,
and actually I'll add

00:21:29.783 --> 00:21:34.018
independence at the
higher education level;

00:21:34.018 --> 00:21:35.193
that to some degree the reason why you

00:21:35.193 --> 00:21:37.996
become a professor at
university is that obviously

00:21:37.996 --> 00:21:39.465
you get a lot of intellectual stimulation,

00:21:39.465 --> 00:21:41.059
but you get a ton of respect,

00:21:41.059 --> 00:21:42.726
and you get a lot of independence,

00:21:42.726 --> 00:21:45.257
especially once you get tenure.

00:21:45.257 --> 00:21:50.115
I think the solution
here is get compensation,

00:21:50.115 --> 00:21:51.315
compensation is important.

00:21:51.315 --> 00:21:53.054
Compensation has to go up.

00:21:53.054 --> 00:21:54.950
I think it has to at least get comparable

00:21:54.950 --> 00:21:56.448
to university professors.

00:21:56.448 --> 00:22:01.209
This day and age, that's
definitely a lot higher

00:22:01.209 --> 00:22:02.918
than where teachers are paid right now,

00:22:02.918 --> 00:22:05.051
but they don't have to get to
investment banking salaries.

00:22:05.051 --> 00:22:07.118
I think even more importantly,
they have to be fields

00:22:07.118 --> 00:22:09.610
where teachers can
express their creativity

00:22:09.610 --> 00:22:14.671
and they're given much
more power and respect

00:22:14.671 --> 00:22:17.872
than, in a lot of cases,
they're given right now.

00:22:17.872 --> 00:22:19.345
Definitely even independence.

00:22:19.345 --> 00:22:21.203
I think this is a role that we have.

00:22:21.203 --> 00:22:23.946
Every iteration, every
time government officials

00:22:23.946 --> 00:22:25.445
panic about the education system,

00:22:25.445 --> 00:22:26.733
they just micromanage it more.

00:22:26.733 --> 00:22:28.946
That might, in their minds,

00:22:28.946 --> 00:22:30.607
de-risk the worst that's going on,

00:22:30.607 --> 00:22:32.667
but it also handicaps
the best that's going on.

00:22:32.667 --> 00:22:37.693
It forces teachers to
lose their independence.

